wiki.content: “Changes” is by Justin Bieber, and is the title track, featured on his fifth studio album of the same name. Billboard said about the track: "In the song "Changes", it actually talks about how some days we want to push further and some days we feel like doing nothing. And that often comes with a mood and an attitude towards life. Sometimes when life throws you things you can’t control and naturally your attitude is to be upset or to be disappointed or discouraged. But when you fight through those feelings that are just feelings in the end of the day you choose to put your effort into your work or into your passion and find that drive .. Life is worth living. And if you’re not going to give up the only thing to do is push forward." - via Billboard (2020) Throughout the song, Bieber keeps the same subject, talking about different circumstances in life. His message states that he is going through changes, like he says in the chorus. In the outro, Bieber states that people change. An example of a change is the 2019-20 coronavirus pandemic in the world. However, at the time of this song’s release, it was not a pandemic. Read more on Last.fm.
